@description.body: A virtual form widget that allows text entry as well as selection from a drop-down.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: String value which will be shown as a hint if the field is all of: unset, unfocused and enabled. Set to null to not show a placeholder text.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Formatting function that will be applied to the value of a selected model item's label before it is written to the text field. Also used to find and preselect the first list entry that begins with the current content of the text field when the drop-down list is opened. Can be used e.g. to strip HTML tags from rich-formatted item labels. The function will be called with the item's label (String) as the only parameter.
